question:
Q1: What is the time complexity of adding a node to the front of a LinkedList?
A. O(1)
B. O(n)
C. O(n^2)
D. O(2^n)

Q2: What is the time complexity of traversing n nodes in a LinkedList?
A. O(1)
B. O(n)
C. O(n^2)
D. O(2^n)

Q3: What is an advantage of using an array over an ArrayList?
A. Primitives
B. Size
C. Gaps in data
D. Chain of nodes
answer:
Q1: A. O(1)
Q2: B. O(n)
Q3: A. Primitives
